parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Power steering assist fault warning light illuminates
steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or seize
grinding noise when turning the wheels

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or surge while driving, which can lead to accidents, especially on highways or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: the "wrench" light or "check engine" light comes on
and the vehicle may not accelerate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Failure of LED Brake Light Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the LED brake light assembly can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially lead to safety hazards.
symptoms: The brake light does not illuminate
even when the brake pedal is not depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent or Complete Failure of LED Tail Light Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the LED tail light assembly can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially lead to safety hazards.
symptoms: The tail light does not illuminate
even when the headlights are not on.
